Hudson Avenue, east side, north of Park Avenue, to Concord Street.

August 25, 1925.

P.L. Sperr

Park Avenue, south side, east from Hudson Avenue. The clearance runs east to Navy Street and extends, in this view, south to Tillary Street. The buildings seen directly across the clearance are on Navy Street.

View 1: August 25, 1938
View 2: August 23, 1939

P. L. Sperr

The cleared area was created by the demolition of buildings of Fort Greene Houses.
